description:
Our Apartment is located directly across the street from Reservoir val Park and it's very close to Montefiore Hospital. Conveniently located next to the 4 train and train and Metro North you can get anywhere in the City from here pretty quickly. Very private co-op building and safe neighborhood

Our place as a beautiful Court when you walk into the building with a beautiful garden. Modern state-of-the-art laundry room is available downstairs in the basement which is been newly constructed. Reservoir oval Park is right across the street great for walks jogging exercising playing tennis, basketball or just walking the dog.

There are 2 bedrooms in our place. One bedroom is accessible by the guest and one we use as storage room  which we only access in between reservations.  Guests have access to the entire one bedroom apartment as well as the laundry room located downstairs in the basement. The second bedroom can also be rented for an additional fee.

As much or as little as needed

The diversity of food available is nice as well as having the park directly across the street

Public transportation is super convenient in our area . The 4 train, the D Train, and plenty of buses are available in our vicinity which makes it possible for you to get anywhere in the city really quickly

Plenty of places to eat and order great food  from nearby.

hosts.about:
Hi I'm Andre',
As a young Computer engineer I've always loved Music and Photography. I grew up in the Bronx, NYC.  I like to make / mix beats, work on technology projects, and take beautiful photos.  Laid back, but I'm pretty organized for a guy and like to keep a clean environment.  Natural gamer since young.  I love to write, cook & eat good food.  My Dad is a chef and so naturally I love to cook.  I love this area because there are so many amazing specialty markets in walking distance.  Mrs Greens, Trader Joe's and Hmart are all walking distance.  I believe in keep good energy, and parry negativity.  I like Crystals as you may notice them spread around the house.  I own an electric hybrid and I'm looking forward to going all electric.  I've studied Japanese Martial Arts for a long time and love asian culture.   You'll notice that in the decor.  Love Tai-chi and Yoga.
